    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban house builders including service management for freeholds in the deeds",
        "additional_details": "Because as of recently I bought my first home as a freehold owner and 2 years later I\u2019m being served a bill for \u00a387 every 6months in advance to maintain a tiny patch of grass that isn\u2019t actually communal it\u2019s public as it\u2019s not gated and anyone can walk into the estate and use that grass (what there is of grass at least). I have never used or seen anyone use this \u201ccommunal\u201d area in the whole 2 years at this property.\r\n\r\nIt needs to be against the law to allow house builders to bind this into deeds",
        "background": "Ban the sale of management services & fees of freehold property owners to management companies. As they are Charging extortionate amounts for stuff we will never use.",
